{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The plant hormone auxin (indole-3-acetic acid) can regulate the gene expression of several families, including Aux/IAA, GH3 and SAUR families. Two related families of proteins, Aux/IAA proteins ([interpro:IPR003311]) and the auxin response factors (ARF), are key regulators of auxin-modulated gene expression [[cite:PUB00014766]]. There are multiple ARF proteins, some of which activate, while others repress transcription. ARF proteins bind to auxin-responsive cis-acting promoter elements (AuxREs) using an N-terminal DNA-binding domain. It is thought that Aux/IAA proteins activate transcription by modifying ARF activity through the C-terminal protein-protein interaction domains found in both Aux/IAA and ARF proteins.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4ldv", "name" "Crystal structure of the DNA binding domain of A. thailana auxin response factor 1"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR31384" "AUXIN RESPONSE FACTOR 4-RELATED"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Auxin response factor", "short" "ARF_plant"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 13, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 250, "taxa" 1168, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 15368, "sets" 0, "proteins" 15368, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 9249}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR044835", :literature {"PUB00014766" {"URL" nil, "issue" "3-4", "authors" ["Liscum E" "Reed JW."], "ISO_journal" "Plant Mol. Biol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1023/A:1015255030047", "medline_journal" "Plant Mol Biol", "title" "Genetics of Aux/IAA and ARF action in plant growth and development.", "year" 2002, "raw_pages" "387-400", "volume" "49", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 12036262}}, :go-terms [{"identifier" "GO:0003677", "name" "DNA binding", "category" {"code" "F", "name" "molecular